# Project Licensing: The L-Exponential Model (V1)

This repository applies a dual-licensing strategy to accommodate a diverse, non-commercial ecosystem of researchers and developers while protecting the core framework from commercial exploitation.

---

## 1. Documentation & Theoretical Framework (Texts, Equations, Appendices)
All written documentation, mathematical models, and theoretical descriptions in this repository are licensed under:
👉 Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)
* Attribution: You must give appropriate credit to Dr. Mohamed Al-Qahiri.
* Non-Commercial: You may not use the material for commercial purposes.
* ShareAlike: If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you must distribute your contributions under the same license.

---

## 2. Source Code, Demos, and Smart Contracts
All functional source code, scripts, software simulations, and smart contracts in this repository are licensed under:
👉 PolyForm Noncommercial License 1.0.0
* Permitted Use: You may use, modify, and distribute this software for any non-commercial purpose (educational, personal, research, or non-profit organization deployment).
* Commercial Restrictions: Any commercial use, including offering the software as a service (SaaS) or using it within a for-profit entity, requires a separate, written commercial license from the author.
